    <item>
      <title>Why Arguments Are Important for Personal Growth and Spirituality?</title>
      <link>/wiaposts/is-argument-bad/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 17 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/is-argument-bad/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5291-is-argument-bad.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Is Argument Bad?&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Is Argument Bad? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;is-argument-bad&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#is-argument-bad&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this talk I will discuss with about &amp;ldquo;Argument&amp;rdquo;&lt;br&gt;
People think Argument is bad. &lt;br&gt;
You can think, and ask yourself, &lt;br&gt;
Is Argument really bad? &lt;br&gt;
We will discussed that here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An argument is a structured series of&lt;br&gt;
sentences, statements, or propositions,&lt;br&gt;
where some serve as premises leading to a conclusion.&lt;br&gt;
This logical framework is not just confined&lt;br&gt;
to philosophy or debate but is also fundamental to both&lt;br&gt;
scientific inquiry and spiritual exploration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>How to Overcome the Ego and Find Joy in Life?</title>
      <link>/wiaposts/overcome-ego-and-find-joy-in-life/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 16 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/overcome-ego-and-find-joy-in-life/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5290-overcome-ego-and-find-joy-in-life.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Ego and Joy of Life&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Ego and Joy of Life 
    &lt;div id=&#34;ego-and-joy-of-life&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#ego-and-joy-of-life&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think, &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;The ego within us &lt;br&gt;
wants to do something difficult because, &lt;br&gt;
against the difficult, one feels, &lt;br&gt;
&amp;lsquo;I am someone, doing such a difficult thing,&amp;rsquo;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;
then think again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is not about seeking difficulty. &lt;br&gt;
If you challenge someone by asking, &lt;br&gt;
&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Why are you doing X in the most difficult way?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;br&gt;
they will likely respond, &lt;br&gt;
&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;This is the easiest and simplest way.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
